==Translingual==
===Etymology===
From {{Gr.}} prefix [[σχιζο-]] ([[schizo-]]), from [[Ancient Greek]] [[σκίζω]] (schizo) "to tear, to split" + [[-phyta]]

===Proper noun===
'''Schizophyta'''

#{{cattag|Botany|Obsolete}}: A [[botanical name]] for a [[taxon]] that includes the [[bacteria]] and [[cyanobacterium|cyanobacteria]]. The taxon is traditionally given the [[rank]] of a [[division]].

